STAAR is funded through both the Better Assistance in Crisis (BASIC) programme and the Gender-Responsive Social Protection (GSP) programme and provides independent, expert technical assistance, advice and resources to support the individual, institutional and global changes that are needed to realise the visions of the GSP and BASIC programmes. STAAR support aims to increase and expand the use of social protection approaches in crises and social protection systems that respond to the needs of women and girls across their lives.
